    "comment": "Rationale: Abl-interacting protein-1 (ABI-1)/Abi1, is a component of the WAVE complex, that organizes the actin cytoskeleton and promotes vesicle clustering at presynaptic sites. Using a mutant allele of abi-1 in C. elegans, the authors showed defective vesicle clustering at presynaptic sites.. Experimental description: Worms were raised on NGM plates at 20°C using OP50 Escherichia coli as a food source. N2 Bristol was used as the wild-type reference strain.",
